steps.instruction:
### Steps
1. Finely Chop cilantro
2. Combine cilantro with the mayo in a marge bowl
3. Zest the lime peel (no white, for about 1 teaspoon)
4. Squeeze the limes for the juice (about 2 tablespoons)
5. Add both to the mayo mix
6. Add Slaw to mix
7. Stir to combine
8. Combine the ranch dressing and shrimp
9. Toss to coat
10. Put fry mix into a bowl
11. Place the shrimp in the fry mix bowl and cover them in the mix
12. Preheat a large saute pan on medium high for 3 to 4 minutes
13. Place oil in the pan
14. Add shrimps to the pan, cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side
15. Drain the shrimp on a paper towel
16. Microwave the tortillas for 25 seconds on high
17. Peel avocado and slice thinly 
18. In each tortillas place avocado, shrimp, and slaw
